 :tx/rationale "Create task: CE-CONN: Auto-connection of observations via keyword Jaccard with hub-preferential attachment. CONTEXT: Observations enter as isolated islands. CRB already tokenizes text and computes Jaccard for duplicate detection. Same machinery repurposed to PROPOSE connections. RATIONALE: FEGH needs a connected graph. Without connections, FEGH has nothing to work with on external projects. Auto-connection provides the graph structure that enables bridge hypothesis generation. N*log(N) hub routing ensures value scales correctly. APPROACH: (1) Add connect_to_existing(store, new_observation_entity, session_boundary_tx) -> Vec<ConnectionDatom> in a new module crates/braid-kernel/src/connections.rs. (2) Tokenize the new observation's :exploration/body (reuse CRB's tokenize_for_jaccard or equivalent). (3) Iterate over existing session observations (entities with :exploration/body asserted after session_boundary_tx). For each, compute pairwise Jaccard similarity. (4) Hub identification: count existing :connection/* datoms per observation entity. Observations with more connections are hubs. (5) Preferential attachment: sort candidates by jaccard_score * (1 + log(1 + connection_degree)). Select top-log(N) connections (N = session observation count). (6) For each selected connection: create :connection/{hash} entity with :connection/source (Ref), :connection/target (Ref), :connection/weight (Double = Jaccard score), :connection/temporal-proximity (Double), :connection/cross-agent (Boolean), :connection/hebbian-boost (Double, ADR-029). (7) Connection threshold: base = 0.10 (configurable). Cross-agent connections get 0.5x threshold (lower bar = more cross-agent links). (8) Wire into braid observe pipeline: after recording observation datoms, call connect_to_existing and write connection datoms in same transaction or follow-up tx. (9) Schema: add :connection/* attributes to runtime schema (extend install_runtime_schema or add install_connection_schema). ACCEPTANCE: (A) After 8 observations with keyword overlap, at least 3 :connection/* entities created. (B) Hub observations (connected to 3+) have higher connection degree than leaves. (C) Cross-agent observations connected at lower threshold. (D) No connections created for unrelated observations (Jaccard < 0.10). (E) O(N*log(N)) performance: 100 observations processed in <1s. (F) Connection datoms queryable via standard Datalog. DEPENDS-ON: CE-BOOT (bootstrap provides first observations to connect). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/connections.rs (new) + crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs"
